</ref> William Harmon, a [[pimp]] in 1981, testified in an August 1996 post-conviction relief hearing that he had seen a man other than Abu-Jamal execute Faulkner and flee in a car which pulled up at the crimescene.<ref name = "aic">{{cite web
 | last =
 | first =
 | authorlink =
 | coauthors =
 | title =Notes on the criminal case of Mumia Abu-Jamal -defense witnesses
