In corroboration of the four prosecution eyewitnesses, Robert Harkins testified on [[August 2]], [[1995]], that he had witnessed a man stand over Faulkner as the latter lay wounded on the ground, who shot him point-blank in the face and who then "walked and sat down on the curb."<ref>{{cite web
