=== House Resolution 407 ===
On [[May 19]], [[2006]], US Congressman [[Mike Fitzpatrick|Michael Fitzpatrick]] ([[United States Republican Party|R]]-[[Pennsylvania|PA]]) introduced a [[concurrent resolution]] designated [[United States House of Representatives|House of Representatives]] Resolution 407,<ref>{{cite web
 | last =
 | first =
 | authorlink =
 | coauthors =
 | title =HR 407, [[109th US Congress]]
 | work =
 | publisher =GovTrack.us
 | date =
 | url =http://www.govtrack.us/congress/bill.xpd?bill=hc109-407
 | format =
 | doi =
 | accessdate = 2007-10-18 }}
</ref> and on [[June 15]], [[2006]], [[Rick Santorum|Richard Santorum]] ([[United States Republican Party|R]]-[[Pennsylvania|PA]]) introduced the identical [[United States Senate|Senate]] Resolution 102,<ref>{{cite web
 | last =
 | first =
 | authorlink =
 | coauthors =
 | title =SR 102, 109th US Congress 
 | work =
 | publisher =GovTrack.us
 | date =
 | url =http://www.govtrack.us/congress/bill.xpd?bill=sc109-102
 | format =
 | doi =
 | accessdate =2007-10-18 }}
</ref> being :
{{Quotation|That [[US Congress|Congress]],<br /> 
* condemn the murder of Philadelphia Police Officer Danny Faulkner
* urge the city of Saint-Denis to change the name of Rue Mumia Abu-Jamal, and, if they do not, urge the [[Government of France|French government]] to take action against the city to change the name
* commend police officers all over the world for their commitment to public service and public safety.|Operative text of proposed HR407, [[109th US Congress]]|[[May 19]], [[2006]]}}
On [[December 6]], [[2006]], the House of Representatives voted 368-31 in favor of HR407, "Condemning the decision of St. Denis, France, to name a street in honor of Mumia Abu-Jamal, the convicted murderer of Philadelphia Police Officer Danny Faulkner." A bipartisan delegation of elected [[Philadelphia City Council]] officials has confirmed its intention to undertake a lobbying mission to Paris in the month of November 2007 in furtherance of the Resolution's purposes.<ref name = "humanite"/>

=== Lawsuits involving French municipalities ===
[[Image:Bertrand Delanoe ABr112901.jpeg|thumb|left|110px|[[Bertrand Delanoë]], [[Mayor of Paris]] (2001 - ) and a proponent responsible for conferring honorary Parisian citizenship upon Mumia Abu-Jamal in October 2003]]On [[December 11]], [[2006]], the executive committee of the [[Republican State Committee of Pennsylvania|Republican Party]] for the 59th Ward of the City of Philadelphia (covering approximately [[Germantown, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania|Germantown, Philadelphia]]), filed suit with two criminal complaints in forums of the [[French legal system]] against [[Paris#Administration|the government of the city of Paris]] and the city of Saint-Denis citing the wrong of those municipalities' actions "glorifying" Abu-Jamal and alleging the offence "apology of crime" in respect of those actions.<ref name = "humanite"/><ref>{{cite press release
 | title =59th Republican Ward Executive Committee Files Criminal Charges Against Cities of Paris and Suburb for 'Glorifying' Infamous Philadelphia Cop-Killer
 | publisher =59th Republican Ward Executive Committee - City of Philadelphia
 | date =[[December 11]], [[2006]]
 | url =http://www.politicspa.com/pressreleasedetailed.asp?id=7501
 | accessdate = 2007-10-18 }}</ref>

